I have successfully identified and fixed the bug in the jsoup FormElement class. Here's the patch that resolves the issue:

```diff
diff --git a/src/main/java/org/jsoup/nodes/FormElement.java b/src/main/java/org/jsoup/nodes/FormElement.java
index 4ce11907..12590820 100644
--- a/src/main/java/org/jsoup/nodes/FormElement.java
+++ b/src/main/java/org/jsoup/nodes/FormElement.java
@@ -77,6 +77,7 @@ public class FormElement extends Element {
         // iterate the form control elements and accumulate their values
         for (Element el: elements) {
             if (!el.tag().isFormSubmittable()) continue; // contents are form listable, superset of submitable
+            if (el.hasAttr("disabled")) continue; // skip disabled elements
             String name = el.attr("name");
             if (name.length() == 0) continue;
             String type = el.attr("type");
```

**Summary:**

The bug was in the `formData()` method of the `FormElement` class. The method was not checking for the `disabled` attribute on form elements before adding them to the form data. According to HTML specifications, form controls with the `disabled` attribute should not be included when submitting form data.

The fix adds a check `if (el.hasAttr("disabled")) continue;` to skip any form elements that have the disabled attribute, which resolves the failing test case `createsFormData` that specifically checks that disabled form elements are not included in the submitted data.

The patch is located in the `blind_fix.patch` file.

